</DOCHDR>
<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>5.5 Help Wanted for Lunar Sample ReturnProgram</TITLE></HEAD><body bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><!-- Artemis Data Book --><!-- ADB section 5.5 Lunar Sample Return --><!-- file: /adb/05/05/help-wanted.html --><!-- v 1.0 --><h2 align="center">Artemis Data Book</H2><h2 align="center">5.5 Lunar Sample Return</H2><h2 align="center">Help Wanted for Lunar Sample Return Program</H2><p align=center><I>Gregory R. Bennett</I></P><P><HR><P><P>To put the Lunar Sample Return program together, we need to get itorganized.  Thatstarts with finding the key people to manage the effort.  While thisinitial effort will be done by <ahref="/adb/06/royalties-for-volunteers.html">volunteers</a>, there is ofcourse theopportunty for <a href="/adb/03/09/">employment</a> in the resultingcommercial enterprise if wedecide to go ahead with this program, and the opportunity to set up yourown business and execute the plan with as much help as the <ahref="/artemis.html">Artemis Project</a>can provide.  Of course, we can't promise employment to anyone.  It's achance to show what you can do and find out if this is really what you wantto do.</P><P><HR><P><H3>Lunar Sample Return Program Manager</H3><P><B>Task Description</B>:<BR>General Manager of a program to recover samples fromEarth's moon and market them on Earth as a commercial product.  Assembleand lead a team to develop the program in sufficient detail to go publicwith a business plan and private offering for investment.</P><P><B>Skills Required</B>:<BR>Experience in commercial business management, andespecially program management, is required.  Experience in commercialaerospace, especially unmanned space flight, and product marketing ishighly desirable.  Ability to organize and collaborate with a world-wideteam via electronic mail is required.</P><P><B>Organization</B>: Artemis Society International Office of BusinessManagement</P><P><B>Compensation</B>: None; this is a volunteer effort.</P><P><B>Contact</B>:<BR>Boise Pearson <a href="mailto:boise@asi.org">&lt;boise@asi.org&gt;</A>,<BR>President and Chairman of the Board<BR><a href="/asi_index.html">Artemis Society International</a></P><P><HR><P><H3>Lunar Sample Market Survey Team Lead</H3><P><B>Task Description</B>:<BR>Define approach to conducting market surveys todetermine revenues from the sale of moon rocks and dust as commercialproducts.  Assemble a team and lead the effort to get the market surveysdone.  Develop estimated revenues from payloads of lunar samples.</P><P><B>Skills Required</B>:<BR>Experience in market surveys; product marketing;collectables, jewelry, geology, planetarium or museum management, wholesalemerchandising are all desirable.  Experience in leading a team is highlydesirable.  Ability to organize and collaborate with a world-wide team viaelectronic mail is required.</P><P><B>Organization</B>: Artemis Society International Office of BusinessManagement</P><P><B>Compensation</B>: None; this is a volunteer effort.</P><P><B>Contact</B>:<BR>Boise Pearson <a href="mailto:boise@asi.org">&lt;boise@asi.org&gt;</A>,<BR>President and Chairman of the Board<BR><a href="/asi_index.html">Artemis Society International</a></P><P><HR><P><H3>Lunar Sample Return Spacecraft Design Team Lead</H3><P><B>Task Description</B>:<BR>Lead a team to develop spacecraft and mission plansfor lunar sample return spacecraft.</P><P><B>Skills Required</B>:<BR>Experience in mission planning for spacecraft isrequired.  Experience in leading an engineering team, teaching, andcommercial aerospace engineering are highly desirable.  Experience in thefundamentals of spacecraft design is required.  Ability to organize andcollaborate with a world-wide team via electronic mail is required.</P><P><B>Organization</B>: Artemis Society International Office of Space Flight</P><P><B>Compensation</B>: None; this is a volunteer effort.</P><P><B>Contact</B>:<BR>Candace Dicks<a href="mailto:CDDicks@aol.com">&lt;CDDicks@aol.com&gt;</a>,<BR>Administrator, Office of Space Flight<BR><a href="/asi_index.html">Artemis Society International</A></P><!-- Nav Bar --><hr size="5"><table align=center border=4 cellpadding = 3 cellspacing=2><tr><td align=center> <b><a href="http://www.asi.org/index.html">ArtemisProject</a></b><td align=center> <b><a href="http://www.asi.org/asi_index.html">ArtemisSociety</a></b><td align=center> <b><a href="http://www.asi.org/adb/index.html">ArtemisData Book</a></b><td align=center> <b><a href="/adb/j/index.html">FAQ</a></b><td align=center> <b><a href="/adb/04/index.html">Reference Mission</a></b><td align=center> <b><a href="http://www.tlrc.com/catalog.html">Catalog</a></b></tr></table><hr size="5"><font size=-2>Copyright &#169; 1996 Artemis Society International.Updated Thu, Arp 18, 1996<br>Content by <a href="/bios/bennett.gregory.html">Gregory R. Bennett</a> <ahref="mailto:grb@asi.org">&lt;grb@asi.org&gt;</a>, maintained by <AHREF="MAILTO:simon@eagle.ca">&lt;simon@eagle.ca&gt;</A>.<br>"<a href="/Artemis.html">The Artemis Project</a>"is a trademark of <aHREF="http://www.tlrc.com/Lrc.html">The Lunar Resources Company</a>.</font></body></html>
