<HTML><HEAD>
<TITLE>1.2 How Do We Know When We're Done?</TITLE> </HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<!-- Artemis Data Book section 1.2 Vision of the Artemis Project -->
<!-- file: /adb/01/02/exploration-scenario.html -->
<!-- Keywords: future mars moon lunacity star travel long-term -->
<H2 ALIGN="center">Artemis Data Book</H2>
<H2 ALIGN="center">1.2 Vision of the Artemis Project</H2>
<H2 ALIGN="center">How Do We Know When We're Done?</H2>
<P><HR><P>

<P>We don't.</P>
<P>Like Disneyland, the Artemis Project will never be finished. The skeleton
scenario for the Artemis Project is something like:</P>
<OL>

<LI>Several very small robotic explorers, leading to . . .<P>
  </P></LI>
<LI>First lunar exploration base (a small module), leading to . . .<P>
  </P></LI>
<LI>Lunar exploration and site assays, in parallel with . . . <P>   </P></LI>
<LI>Lunar industrial process pilot plants, leading to . . .<P>
  </P></LI>
<LI>Lunar industries expansion at the exploration base, leading to . . .<P>
  </P></LI>
<LI>Exploration base expansion, leading to . . .<P>
  </P></LI>
<LI>Subselene village, in parallel with . . .<P>   </P></LI>
<LI>Reduced-cost manned launchers, in parallel with . . .<P>   </P></LI>
<LI>Expansion of lunar fuels industry, leading to . . .<P>
  </P></LI>
<LI>Lunar tourism, leading to . . .<P>
  </P></LI>
<LI>Subselene city, in parallel with . . . <P>   </P></LI>
<LI>Farside scientific outposts, leading to . . .<P>
  </P></LI>
<LI>Lunar surface transportation systems, leading to . . .<P>
  </P></LI>
<LI>Self-sufficient lunar economy, and . . .  <P>   </P></LI>
<LI>More cities, leading to . . .<P>
  </P></LI>
<LI>Support to planetary exploration, leading to . . .<P>
  </P></LI>
<LI>Human communities on Mars, and . . .<P>   </P></LI>
<LI>Asteroid mining, leading to . . .<P>
  </P></LI>
<LI>Human communities in the asteroid belt, leading to . . .<P>
  </P></LI>
<LI>Human communities among the outer planets, leading to . . .<P>
</P><P>THE STARS!</P></LI>
</OL><!-- Nav Bar -->
