<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>1.2 Requirements of Moonbase Artemis</TITLE></HEAD><body bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><!-- Artemis Data Book --><!-- ADB section 1.2 Vision --><!-- file: /adb/01/02/moonbase-requirements.html           /adb/02/01/moonbase-requirements.html--><!-- Keywords: Artemis Project frontier vision goals commercail mannedspace development company money --><!-- v 1.0 --><h2 align="center">Artemis Data Book</H2><h2 align="center">1.2 Vision</H2><h2 align="center">2.1 Expanding the Lunar Base</H2><h2 align="center">Requirements of Moonbase Artemis</H2><P><HR><P><P>Ultimately we want to see a thriving spacefaring community.  Besides <ahref="/adb/04/02/05/04/">digging up moon dirt</a> and <ahref="/adb/02/02/">separating</a> out the good stuff, that includes <ahref="/adb/02/06/">people living</a> on the <a href="/adb/02/01">moon</a>,in <a HREF="/adb/02/06/">space</a>, on space stations (or colonies, ifthey're feasible), building powersats (if they're feasible), <ahref="/adb/01/02/asteroid-mission-notes.html">mining asteroids</a>,building communities on Mars, <a href="/adb/02/05/">exploring the outerplanets</a>, conducting exploration and scientific research in all theseenvironments, and doing whatever it is people want to do.</P><P>There are a host of options to choose from.  The path we take indevelopment of a lunar base to achieve that grand vision is notwell-defined.  However, we don't have to narrow down that field right now.We have sufficient information to define the basic requirements for thecore of a lunar base.  No matter what path we take, the initial lunar basemust:<OL><LI><P>Support visiting crews and keep them happy and healthy<UL>  <LI>We'll probably learn most of what we need to know for long-termhabitation of the moon by providing this function</UL><LI><P>Be indefinitely maintainable<LI><P>Have an open architecture for upgrades to any system<UL>  <LI>We'll want to close the <ahref="/adb/04/03/05/consumable-reduction.html">life support loop</a> asquickly as we can to reduce resupply requirements  <LI>If computer systems continue to become obsolescent as they are doingnow, we might be replacing large chunks of the electronics on every flight</UL><LI><P>Support <a href="/adb/04/03/08/">lunar surface EVA</A><LI><P>Provide power, data, communications, and <a href="/adb/02/05/">lifesupport</a> for the crew<LI><P>Support <a href="/adb/02/02/">regolith mining</a><LI><P>Support exploitation of in-situ material<ul>  <LI><a href="/adb/04/03/10/04/">Oxygen extraction</a>, at least as aleveraging factor for future flights to and from the moon  <LI>Metals extraction, to capitalize on the mass that's there</UL><LI><P>Support space traffic to and from the moon<ul>  <LI>Landing sites  <LI>Landing support systems, such as radio beacons  <LI>Navigation systems; perhaps several radio beacons on the surface</UL><LI><P>Support industrial processes on the moon<ul>  <LI>Storage and garages for external equipment</ul><LI><P>Look neat</P></OL><P>Exactly what the external equipment will be depends on what we learn alongthe way.  If we can afford it, or if we need a large population on the moonright away, we might put priority on searching for a big cavern where we canestablish a large, permanent community.  Alternatively, if we can automate alot of the processing and have customers for <ahref="/adb/04/03/10/04/">lunar oxygen</a>, we'll want to putour priorties on those industrial processes and a launch system to getpayloads off the moon.</P><!-- Nav Bar --><hr size="5"><table align=center border=4 cellpadding = 3 cellspacing=2><tr><td align=center> <b><a href="http://www.asi.org/index.html">ArtemisProject</a></b><td align=center> <b><a href="http://www.asi.org/asi_index.html">ArtemisSociety</a></b><td align=center> <b><a href="http://www.asi.org/adb/index.html">ArtemisData Book</a></b><td align=center> <b><a href="/adb/j/index.html">FAQ</a></b><td align=center> <b><a href="/adb/04/index.html">Reference Mission</a></b><td align=center> <b><a href="http://www.tlrc.com/catalog.html">Catalog</a></b></tr></table><hr size="5"><font size=-2>Copyright &#169; 1996 Artemis Society International.Updated Sun, Mar 31, 1996<br>Content by <a href="/bios/bennett.gregory.html">Gregory R. Bennett</a> <ahref="mailto:grb@asi.org">&lt;grb@asi.org&gt;</a>, maintained by <AHREF="MAILTO:simon@eagle.ca">&lt;simon@eagle.ca&gt;</A>.<br>"<a href="/Artemis.html">The Artemis Project</a>"is a trademark of <aHREF="http://www.tlrc.com/Lrc.html">The Lunar Resources Company</a>.</font></body></html>
