<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>3.3 Space Fantasy and Real Space</TITLE></HEAD><body bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><!-- Artemis Data Book --><!-- ADB section 3.3 Financing the Project --><!-- file: /adb/03/03/fact-fiction.html --><!-- Keywords: habitat robot Carnegie-Mellon University Lunacorp regolithheat insulation bury --><!-- v 1.0 --><h2 align="center">Artemis Data Book</H2><h2 align="center">3.3 Financing the Project</H2><h2 align="center">Space Fantasy and Real Space</H2><P ALIGN=CENTER><I>Gregory R. Bennett</I></P><P><HR><P><P>Our goal is to separate far-outscience fiction from space travel in the audience's mind.  People like towatch car chases on television, but about 1% of that adventure is more thanenough in one's personal life.  That's why Apollo 13 was as exciting asStar Wars -- it's not the same thing.  Star Wars isn't about space travel;it's a fantasy story in a universe where magic works about the strugglebetween Good and Evil.  Apollo 13 was a real, human adventure, so it waseven more emotionally gripping than the space-fantasy flicks.</P><P>That's why I keep saying that the Big Difference is that the ArtemisProject is <I>real</I>!</p><P>Fantasy stories are big sellers, but I've found people get moreinvolved with the characters in my hard-sf stories because the situationsare more real.  They can identify with the adventure.  If the big fantasywas what people just had to have, all the guys in the U.S. would move toLas Vegas and chase showgirls instead of pursuing the girl next door; orthey'd stay home and watch videos.</P><P>Maybe some day virtual reality will be so realistic that it is assatisfying as real life, but we'll need a new revolution in physics forthat to happen.  And even then, a canned script just won't be the same asthe real thing.</P><!-- Nav Bar --><hr size="5"><table align=center border=4 cellpadding = 3 cellspacing=2><tr><td align=center> <b><a href="http://www.asi.org/index.html">ArtemisProject</a></b><td align=center> <b><a href="http://www.asi.org/asi_index.html">ArtemisSociety</a></b><td align=center> <b><a href="http://www.asi.org/adb/index.html">ArtemisData Book</a></b><td align=center> <b><a href="/adb/j/index.html">FAQ</a></b><td align=center> <b><a href="/adb/04/index.html">Reference Mission</a></b><td align=center> <b><a href="http://www.tlrc.com/catalog.html">Catalog</a></b></tr></table><hr size="5"><font size=1>Copyright &#169; 1996 Artemis Society International.Updated Mon, Sep 2, 1996<br>Content by <a href="/bios/bennett.gregory.html">Gregory R. Bennett</a> <ahref="mailto:grb@asi.org">&lt;grb@asi.org&gt;</a>, maintained by <AHREF="MAILTO:simon@eagle.ca">&lt;simon@eagle.ca&gt;</A>.<br>"<a href="/Artemis.html">The Artemis Project</a>"is a trademark of <aHREF="http://www.tlrc.com/Lrc.html">The Lunar ResourcesCompany</a>.</font></body></html>
