<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>3.3 LRC License Sales</TITLE></HEAD><body bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><!-- Artemis Data Book --><!-- ADB section 3.3 Financing the Project --><!-- file: /adb/03/03/lrc-license-sales.html --><!-- v 1.0 --><h2 align="center">Artemis Data Book</H2><h2 align="center">3.3 Financing the Project</H2><h2 align="center">LRC License Sales</H2><P ALIGN=CENTER><I>Gregory R. Bennett</I></P><P><HR><P><P><a href="http://www.tlrc.com/">The Lunar Resources Company</A> isworking on license sales, but the value of the license is basedon publicity for the Artemis Project.  Products like a screen saverincrease the exposure, so they are part of the rising tide which raises allships.</p><P>Licensing definitely comes under LRC's domain.  Financial arrangementsare worked out in a case-by-case basis.  Yes, we have guidelines forlicensings fees; but no, I won't make them public.  We haven't attempted aprogram of recognizing ASI as an agent, however individuals who might alsobe members of the <a href="/asi_index.html">Artemis Society</a> are welcometo pursue licensing contracts and hence earn a finders fee when the fish islanded.</P><P>Money from licenses sold by LRC goes into the pool set aside by LRC asa commitment to purchase stock in the space flight company when that stockbecomes available.  Similarly, any money raised by Artemis SocietyInternational goes into ASI's fund, which is also committed to purchasingstock in the space flight company.  Also, individuals may commit topurchasing stock in the space flight company.  Which of these methods --commercial, donations, or direct investment -- will be most effective isleft for future history to decide.  Hitting it on all fronts seems thefastest way to the moon.</P><P>LRC's <a href="/adb/03/sponsorship.html">sponsorship</a> of ASI isaccounted for separately, to maintain the think tank and the playground aswell as the pro bono contribution toward education and science.</P><!-- Nav Bar --><hr size="5"><table align=center border=4 cellpadding = 3 cellspacing=2><tr><td align=center> <b><a href="http://www.asi.org/index.html">ArtemisProject</a></b><td align=center> <b><a href="http://www.asi.org/asi_index.html">ArtemisSociety</a></b><td align=center> <b><a href="http://www.asi.org/adb/index.html">ArtemisData Book</a></b><td align=center> <b><a href="/adb/j/index.html">FAQ</a></b><td align=center> <b><a href="/adb/04/index.html">Reference Mission</a></b><td align=center> <b><a href="http://www.tlrc.com/catalog.html">Catalog</a></b></tr></table><hr size="5"><font size=1>Copyright &#169; 1996 Artemis Society International.Updated Mon, Sept 9, 1996<br>Content by <a href="/bios/bennett.gregory.html">Gregory R. Bennett</a> <ahref="mailto:grb@asi.org">&lt;grb@asi.org&gt;</a>, maintained by <AHREF="MAILTO:simon@eagle.ca">&lt;simon@eagle.ca&gt;</A>.<br>"<a href="/Artemis.html">The Artemis Project</a>"is a trademark of <aHREF="http://www.tlrc.com/Lrc.html">The Lunar ResourcesCompany</a>.</font></body></html>
