Last-modified: Mon, 09 Sep 1996 19:06:09 GMT
</DOCHDR>
<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>3.3 Capital for Spaceflight</TITLE></HEAD><body bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><!-- Artemis Data Book --><!-- ADB section 3.3 Financing the Project --><!-- file: /adb/03/03/spaceflight-capital.html --><!-- v 1.0 --><h2 align="center">Artemis Data Book</H2><h2 align="center">3.3 Financing the Project</H2><h2 align="center">Capital for Spaceflight</H2><P ALIGN=CENTER><I>Gregory R. Bennett</I></P><P><HR><P><P>When ASI formally establishes a lunar base development fund,the money will be accumulated to purchase voting stock in a separatecompany (not LRC) formed to design, build, and operate the spacecraft whichestablish the lunar exploration base we've been talking about.</P><P>This ASI fund will not be the sole source of capital for the spaceflight.  Additional stock will be sold to individuals or companies who wantto invest directly in the space flight.  <a href="http://www.tlrc.com/">TheLunar Resources Company</a> is one company which has made a commitment topurchasing stock in this space flight company, based on its earnings fromancillary business ventures associated with the Artemis Project.</P><P>We can't know the most effective way to raise the capital for thisspace flight.  Our original plan was to use the ancillary businesses asthe sole source of capital, and have the entire project done in-house byLRC.  Then many people said they wanted to donate their own effort tomaking it happen; and the <a href="/asi_index.html">Artemis Society</a>grew out of that.  Recently there has been a strong interest in investingdirectly in the space flight.</P><P>The most straightforward solution appears to be to have the spaceflight conducted by a new commercial company, with voting stock availablefor purchase by individuals, by program participants (including LRC), andby Artemis Society International.  We'll write a full prospectus for thiscompany.  Those who read the prospectus and like it will invest in it.Those who don't, won't.</P>