<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>3.3 The Lunar Resources Company's Significance</TITLE></HEAD><body bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><!-- Artemis Data Book --><!-- ADB section 3.3 Financing the Project --><!-- file: /adb/03/03/tlrc-significance.html --><!-- v 1.0 --><h2 align="center">Artemis Data Book</H2><h2 align="center">3.3 Financing the Project</H2><h2 align="center">The Lunar Resources Company's Significance</H2><P ALIGN=CENTER><I>Gregory R. Bennett</I></P><P><HR><P><P>Let me explain why you want to work with <ahref="http://www.tlrc.com/">The Lunar Resources Company</a> to make thisproject happen.</P><P>The Lunar Resources Company's Role in the Artemis Project: The folkswho formed The Lunar Resources Company have taken the personal risk, interms of money, personal reputation, and all of their free time, for yearsto get the Artemis Project going.  To date, all of the people participatingin The Lunar Resources Company have done so with no financial reward atall; some of us forgoing considerable amounts of money to nurture thisprogram.</P><P>For example, my participation in this project continues to cost memany thousands of dollars, both in personal expenses and in earnings I'vehad to forgo because I'm doing Artemis Project things instead of writingstories and doing consulting.</P><P>Without LRC's effort, there would be no Artemis Project.  And withoutthe Artemis Project, the most you could hope for in your lifetime would beone or two commercial robot rovers and just maybe a politically motivatedscientific mission.</P><P>The Lunar Resources Company created <a href="/asi_index.html">ArtemisSociety International</a> and used its own capital to get the organizationgoing.  Without LRC, there would be no Artemis Society, and no way for youto participate in a spaceflight program.  The company continues to underwrite ASI at its own risk.Without The Lunar Resources Company, the Artemis Society is just anotherclub for space fans.</P><P>The Lunar Resources Company has established an international networkof business resources that can take anything created for the ArtemisProject milieu to market more cost-effectively than any other method youmight choose.</P><P>The Lunar Resources Company is the only company committed to investingall its net earnings in the lunar community.  This is LRC's reason forexistence.  We can hope there will be others; indeed others are being setup.</P><H3>About Other Business Ventures</H3><P>Now, having written a sales pitch about The Lunar Resources Company,I have to point out that this can't be a one-company project.</p><P>People are always encouraged to start their own businessventures to participate in the Artemis Project.  That's not a joke;  I'mserious.  We don't have the resources to create every business venture thatit will take to get this thing done.  Besides, the more products andservices are available, the more fun it will be.</P><P>Some folks are tuned to this business stuff; some aren't.  If youcan, please do it.  Those with business talent can create employment forthose with other talents and interests, but <I>somebody</I> has to do thebusiness work.</P><P>If your business can do things with LRC to everyone's benefit, that'sgreat.  But if not, do it anyway; it's still great.  You can conduct yourown business -- be it a corporation, partnership, or sole proprietorship --and have your own Lunar Base Development Fund.  You can use that fund topurchase stock in the moon base, independent of ASI or LRC or anybody else.</P><!-- Nav Bar --><hr size="5"><table align=center border=4 cellpadding = 3 cellspacing=2><tr><td align=center> <b><a href="http://www.asi.org/index.html">ArtemisProject</a></b><td align=center> <b><a href="http://www.asi.org/asi_index.html">ArtemisSociety</a></b><td align=center> <b><a href="http://www.asi.org/adb/index.html">ArtemisData Book</a></b><td align=center> <b><a href="/adb/j/index.html">FAQ</a></b><td align=center> 