<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>3.3 TLRC Stock Issues</TITLE></HEAD><body bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><!-- Artemis Data Book --><!-- ADB section 3.3 Financing the Project --><!-- file: /adb/03/03/tlrc-stock-issues.html --><!-- v 1.0 --><h2 align="center">Artemis Data Book</H2><h2 align="center">3.3 Financing the Project</H2><h2 align="center">TLRC Stock Issues</H2><P ALIGN=CENTER><I>Gregory R. Bennett</I></P><P><HR><P><P>The scenario where preemptive rights are vital to the small investor isa valid concern, but in all likelihood <a href="http://www.tlrc.com">theLunar Resources Comapny</a> Board of Directors doesn't do such a dumbthing.  (In Texas, you can sue someone for stock manipulation.)</P><P>We do have a stock issue strategy in mind.</P><P>Ideally, the corporation would never have to make a new stock issue; itwould use its initial capital and grow until it can afford to complete theproject.  But that would take decades, and I don't think it's in theinterest of stockholders to wait to earn the apparent big profits to bemade from full-scale exploitation of lunar resources.</P><P>So we are looking at a series of stock issues, each timed to provide thenecessary capital to expand into the next phase.  One possiblescenario:</P><PRE>                Technical Development      Business Development                ---------------------      -------------------       Phase 1: Feasibility Study          <ahref="http://www.tlrc.com/artemag/artemis-mag.html">Artemis Magazine</a>                                           <ahref="http://www.tlrc.com/catalog.html">Moon Memorabilia</a>                                           <ahref="/asi_index.html">Artemis Society</a>       Phase 2: Preliminary Design         Expand Moon Memorabilia       Phase 3: Final Design               Films and Video, low market                                           Books                                           Expand Moon Memorabilia       Phase 4: Hardware Construction      Films and Video, mid market                                           Expand other businesses       Phase 5: Flight                     Films and Video, major market                                           Flood souvenir markets       Phase 6: Base Operations            <ahref="/adb/04/03/10/04/oxygen-extraction.html">Lunar Resources</a>       Phase 7: Solar Power Satellites     Power {perhaps}                                           <ahref="/adb/02/07/lunacity-hotel.html">Tourism</a>                                           Space Habitats       Phase 8: Asteroid Mining            Asteroid Resources       (You get the picture)</PRE><P>The more we learn about the business as we go, the better we'll be ableto trim fuzz off predicted revenues.  As a rule, we would like to assurethat the predicted return from each issue of stock is never less than thereturn from that first issue when you bought your 5% of the company,including the time value of the money you invested in 1996.  We can'tguarantee that, of course; others will leap on the bandwagon and dilute ourmarket share as soon as we're successful; but we will forever have themarketing advantage of being the company that made it happen.</P><P>As long as we don't get a greedy Board of Directors who try for the fastbuck, selling schlock at high prices, we will retain a good share of themarket.</P><P>An alternative scenario might include getting into the space launchbusiness if nobody else steps up to it.  Right now, though, I'm assumingthere are enough interested companies that the launchers will happen if wecreate the demand for them.</P><!-- Nav Bar --><hr size="5"><table align=center border=4 cellpadding = 3 cellspacing=2><tr><td align=center> <b><a href="http://www.asi.org/index.html">ArtemisProject</a></b><td align=center> <b><a href="http://www.asi.org/asi_index.html">ArtemisSociety</a></b><td align=center> <b><a href="http://www.asi.org/adb/index.html">ArtemisData 