</DOCHDR>
<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>6. Stress and Manned Space</TITLE></HEAD><body bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><!-- Artemis Data Book --><!-- ADB section 6. Artemis Society --><!-- file: /adb/06/manned-space-stress.html --><!-- v 1.0 --><h2 align="center">Artemis Data Book</H2><h2 align="center">6. Artemis Society</H2><h2 align="center">Stress and Manned Space</H2><P ALIGN=CENTER><I>Gregory R. Bennett</I></P><P><HR><P><P>For Apollo, the toll at the contractors was even worse than the morepublicized lives of the astronauts.  North American had several people dieof heart attacks, and the same malady almost wiped out Harrison Storms, theguy who ran the development of the Apollo command and service modules.</P><P>I see it mostly as a business management issue.  I've said so many timesbefore: use the schedule as a tool, not as an object of worship.</P><P>We'll also have a lower stress level because we don't have to worryabout absorbing the blame for mistakes made by government bureaucrats.  Wedon't have to worry about covering our mistakes; once we get this businessgoing you'll learn I'm the kind of guy who gets worried about someone who'snot willing to make a mistake.  (However, you might also learn that thestress level of someone who berates others for making mistakes can gooff-scale high.  The one mistake I've never tolerated in any organizationI've run is jumping on others for trying to get their work done.)</P><P>Besides that, we're not going to the moon to beat the Russians; we'regoing to the moon because it's fun! </P><!-- Nav Bar --><hr size="5"><table align=center border=4 cellpadding = 3 cellspacing=2><tr><td align=center> <b><a href="http://www.asi.org/index.html">ArtemisProject</a></b><td align=center> <b><a href="http://www.asi.org/asi_index.html">ArtemisSociety</a></b><td align=center> <b><a href="http://www.asi.org/adb/index.html">ArtemisData Book</a></b><td align=center> <b><a href="/adb/j/index.html">FAQ</a></b><td align=center> <b><a href="/adb/04/index.html">Reference Mission</a></b><td align=center> <b><a href="http://www.tlrc.com/catalog.html">Catalog</a></b></tr></table><hr size="5"><font size=1>Copyright &#169; 1996 Artemis Society International.Updated Sat, Apr 15, 1996. OS.0473.28.47#2<br>Content by <a href="/bios/bennett.gregory.html">Gregory R. Bennett</a> <ahref="mailto:grb@asi.org">&lt;grb@asi.org&gt;</a>, maintained by <AHREF="MAILTO:simon@eagle.ca">&lt;simon@eagle.ca&gt;</A>.<br>"<a href="/Artemis.html">The Artemis Project</a>"is a trademark of <aHREF="http://www.tlrc.com/Lrc.html">The Lunar ResourcesCompany</a>.</font></body></html>
