<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>6.3 ASI and Chapter Memberships</TITLE></HEAD><body bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><!-- Artemis Data Book --><!-- ADB section 6.3 Organization --><!-- file: /adb/06/03/chapter-memberships-tasks.html --><!-- Keywords: organisaton ASI artemis society tasks member usefulness endin itself active work --><!-- v 1.0 --><h2 align="center">Artemis Data Book</H2><h2 align="center">6.3 Organization</H2><h2 align="center">ASI and Chapter Memberships and Tasks</H2><P ALIGN=CENTER><I>Boise Pearson</I></P><P><HR><P><P>There are a lot of reasons why not to make action a requirement ofmembership in <a href="/asi_index.html">ASI</a>.  The idea is to have amembership organization that accommodates all the types of members.  Here arethebasic ideas behind it all:</P><ul type=square><LI><P>Only one kind of <a href="/asi_member.html">membership</a>.  Thereisn't a separate membership    for ASI and the <a href="/adb/07/local-chapters.html">localchapters</A>.  To be a member of the local    chapter, you must be a member of ASI.  What we hope to avoid is    a two-tiered membership with only a small portion of the local    membership belonging to the <ahref="/adb/06/">international organization</a>.</P><LI><P>Chapter membership is voluntary.  A member of ASI need never    join a local chapter.  If their interest in joining ASI is just    to belong, then that is what we want them to do.  There is    nothing wrong with that style of membership, and the people    who adopt it are important to ASI for many reasons.</P><LI><P>Chapters with a focus.  When enough members in a local area    get the fever to "do something" to help get us to the moon,    then we would encourage them to form a Local Chapter to focus    their efforts.  People in the area who wanted to be active    participants could join the group (or start their own, with    some other focus in mind) to participate.  It seems that    the most successful local chapters of organizations like    NSS are organized around a specific project or goal (Oregon    L5 studies and promotes lavatubes for lunar bases; Huntsville,    Alabama L5 is building a balloon launched sub-orbital rocket).    We'd like to add a little focus to the local ASI activists    efforts, and encourage the adoption of a project for local    chapters.</P><LI><P>Focus of a Chapter.  Not every local chapter has to design    rockets or moonbases.  ASI-Milwaukee has adopted the publication    of <a href="/mmm">MMM-Pleiades</a>.  Some chapters may want to recruit<a href="/asi_member.html">new members</a>,    handle organizational chores, <a href="artemis96.html">organizeconferences</a>, do publicity,    make displays, design and produce <ahref="http://www.tlrc.com/catalog.html">ASI merchandise</a>, etc.    Whatever reason they had for getting "active" will do.</P></UL><P>So, is this approach reasonable?  Will it help us to appeal to all types of<a href="/asi_member.html">members</a>?  Hopefully we can drive out anyconcerns or problems withthe chapter structure now, so we can start out with the best base possible.</P><!-- Nav Bar --><hr size="5"><table align=center border=4 cellpadding = 3 cellspacing=2><tr><td align=center> <b><a href="http://www.asi.org/index.html">ArtemisProject</a></b><td align=center> <b><a href="http://www.asi.org/asi_index.html">ArtemisSociety</a></b><td align=center> <b><a href="http://www.asi.org/adb/index.html">ArtemisData Book</a></b><td align=center> <b><a href="/adb/j/index.html">FAQ</a></b><td align=center> <b><a href="/adb/04/index.html">Reference Mission</a></b><td align=center> <b><a href="http://www.tlrc.com/catalog.html">Catalog</a></b></tr></table><hr size="5"><font size=-2>Copyright &#169; 1996 Artemis Society International.Updated Fri, Apr 19, 1996<br>Content by Boise Pearson <ahref="mailto:boise@asi.org">&lt;boise@asi.org&gt;</a>, maintained by <AHREF="MAILTO:simon@eagle.ca">&lt;simon@eagle.ca&gt;</A>.<br>"<a href="/Artemis.html">The Artemis Project</a>"is a trademark of <aHREF="http://www.tlrc.com/Lrc.html">The Lunar Resources Company</a>.</font></body></html>
