<html><head><title>6.7.2.1.1 Advanced Planning Tech CommitteeMembership</title></head><body bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><!-- /adb/06/07/02/01/01/aptc.html Lunar Base Advanced Planning Technical Committee --><!-- Keywords: spacecraft propulsion rocket science engine aeronauticalLunar Base Advanced Planning Technical Committee member list--><h2 align=center>Artemis Data Book</h2><h2 align=center>6.7.2.1.1 Lunar Base Advanced Planning Technical Committee</h2><h2 align=center>Advanced Planning Tech Committee Membership</h2><P><HR><P><P>The Lunar Base Advanced Planning Technical Committee is responsible forworking out long-term issues for the Lunar Outpost. History provides manyexamples of the consequences of not planning ahead, and the AdvancePlanning Tech Committee is to avoid costly mistakes. With an entire worldat stake, it is essential to watch the long-term view.</P><UL><LI><B>Members</B> - These are people who are actively involved in thevarious tasks of the APTC. They are doing the actual work of the ProjectTeam itself.<p><LI><B>Reps</B> - To provide a far-reaching influence, there are APTCrepresentatives for other Technical Committees, which keep a long-termframe of mind in important decisions and provide input as to thedevelopments in the Lunar Base Advanced Planning Tech Committee. Reps mayalso be active Members of the SSTO Project Team if they are active in bothcommittees.<p><LI><B>Observers</B> - Not considered official members of the SSTO team,observers are people who want to stay informed of what goes on in the LunarBase Advanced Planning Technical Committee, usually by being included inthe APTC mailing list or related information feeds.</UL><p>If you would like to join the Lunar Base Advanced Planning TechnicalCommittee, fill out and submit the form at the bottom of this page. To seewhat activities are currently going on in the Advanced Planning TC, look atthe <a href="aptc-tasks.html">Advance Planning Task List</a>. Tovolunteer for one of those tasks, fill out and submit the form on the <ahref="aptc-tasks.html">Task List</a> page. The current membership of theLunar Base Advanced Planning Technical Committee is as follows:</P><p><HR><P><h3>Members</h3><table border=0 colspan=2><tr><td>J. Michael Antoniewicz</td><td><a href="mailto:michaela@ncat.edu">&lt;michaela@ncat.edu&gt;</a></td></tr><tr><td>Mark Barbisan</td><td><a href="mailto:barbisan@interlog.com">&lt;barbisan@interlog.com&gt;</a></td></tr><tr><td>Vlado Barun</td><td><a href="mailto:vbarun@andrews.edu">&lt;vbarun@andrews.edu&gt;</a></td></tr><tr><td><a href="http://www.tlrc.com/Bios/bennett.gregory.html">Gregory R.Bennett</a></td><td><a href="mailto:grb@asi.org">&lt;grb@asi.org&gt;</a></td></tr><tr><td>Rick Bier</td><td><a href="mailto:rickbier@axxis.com">&lt;rickbier@axxis.com&gt;</a></td></tr><tr><td>Charles Collier</a></td><td><a href="mailto:cpcollie@seas.gwu.edu">&lt;cpcollie@seas.gwu.edu&gt;</a></td></tr><tr><td>John Drake</td><td><a href="mailto:drakej@epix.net">&lt;drakej@epix.net&gt;</a></td></tr><tr><td><a href="/bios/field.stan.html">Stan Field</a></td><td><a href="mailto:stnfield@gate.net">&lt;stnfield@gate.net&gt;</a></td></tr><tr><td><a href="http://ic.net/~tjh/artemis.html">Tom Hopper</a></td><td><a href="mailto:tjh@ic.net">&lt;73747.1727@compuserve.com&gt;</a></td></tr><tr><td>Peter Kokh</td><td><a href="mailto:kokhmmm@execpc.com">&lt;kokhmmm@execpc.com&gt;</a></td></tr><tr><td>Jim Nobles</td><td><a href="mailto:nobles@asi.org">&lt;nobles@asi.org&gt;</a></td></tr><tr><td>Miki Thompson</td><td><a href="mailto:cabride@aloha.net">&lt;cabride@aloha.net&gt;</a></td></tr><tr><td>Simon Rowland</td><td><a href="mailto:simon@eagle.ca">&lt;simon@eagle.ca&gt;</a></td></tr></table><h3>Reps</h3><table border=0 colspan=3><tr valign=top><tr><td><a href="http://www.tlrc.com/Bios/bennett.gregory.html">Gregory R. Bennett</a>&nbsp; &nbsp; </td><td><a href="mailto:grb@asi.org">&lt;grb