<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>6.7.2.1.3 Lunar Science Tech CommitteeResponsibilities</TITLE></HEAD><body bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><!-- Artemis Data Book --><!-- ADB section 6.7.2.1.3 Lunar Science Technical Committee --><!-- file: /adb/06/07/02/01/03/responsibilities.html --><!-- v 1.0 --><h2 align="center">Artemis Data Book</H2><h2 align="center">6.7.2.1.3 Lunar Science Technical Committee</H2><h2 align="center">Lunar Science Technical Committee Responsibilities</H2><P ALIGN=CENTER><I>Paul J. Morris</I></P><P><HR><P><P>The <a href="/adb/06/07/02/01/03/">Lunar Science Technical Committee</a>serves to compile and summarizeexisting knowledge of the Moon and to identify lunar research projects thatwould directly further the long term goals of the <ahref="/artemis.html">Artemis Project</a>.   The specific areas ofresponsibility for this committee are:</P><oL><P><LI>To provide accurate technical information and sources of additionalinformation concerning conditions on the lunar surface as a resource forother <a href="/adb/06/07/">technical committees</a>.  The committee hasoverall responsibility for<a href="/adb/m/01/">Appendix M</a> of the <a href="/adb/">Artemis DataBook</a>, and will delegate parts of Appendix Mas appropriate to other organizational elements.</P><P><LI>Identify candidate experiments that are directly necessary to further thelong term goals of the Artemis mission or have entertainment value or canbring in external funding/political support.</P><P><LI>Answer specific questions from other organizational elements relevant tolunar science.  </P></OL><!-- Nav Bar --><hr size="5"><table align=center border=4 cellpadding = 3 cellspacing=2><tr><td align=center> <b><a href="http://www.asi.org/index.html">ArtemisProject</a></b><td align=center> <b><a href="http://www.asi.org/asi_index.html">ArtemisSociety</a></b><td align=center> <b><a href="http://www.asi.org/adb/index.html">ArtemisData Book</a></b><td align=center> <b><a href="/adb/j/index.html">FAQ</a></b><td align=center> <b><a href="/adb/04/index.html">Reference Mission</a></b><td align=center> <b><a href="http://www.tlrc.com/catalog.html">Catalog</a></b></tr></table><hr size="5"><font size=1>Copyright &#169; 1996 Artemis Society International.Updated Thu, Jun 6, 1996<br>Content by <a href="/bios/morris.paul.html">Paul J. Morris</a> <ahref="mailto:mole@bio.umass.edu">&lt;mole@bio.umass.edu&gt;</a>, maintainedby <AHREF="MAILTO:simon@eagle.ca">&lt;simon@eagle.ca&gt;</A>.<br>"<a href="/Artemis.html">The Artemis Project</a>"is a trademark of <aHREF="http://www.tlrc.com/Lrc.html">The Lunar ResourcesCompany</a>.</font></body></html>
