<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>6.7.2.1.9. Solar Power Tech Committee Charter</TITLE></HEAD><body bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><!-- Artemis Data Book --><!-- ADB section 6.7.2.1.9. Solar Power Tech Committee --><!-- file: /adb/06/07/02/01/09/charter.html --><!-- v 1.0 --><h2 align="center">Artemis Data Book</H2><h2 align="center">6.7.2.1.9. Solar Power Tech Committee</H2><h2 align="center">Solar Power Tech Committee Charter Beta</H2><P><HR><P><P>The Solar Power Tech Committee is responsible for developing technicalplans and an economic model for solar power as a lunar resource. Thisincludes the economics and design of in-situ manufacturing of solar powercollection apparatus, distribution of power on the Moon and space (to Earthand to spacecraft), examining the possible customer base and the economicsof energy sale, as well as other aspects of the economics of solar power asa lunar resource, and finally a timeline of solar power development.</P><!-- Nav Bar --><hr size="5"><table align=center border=4 cellpadding = 3 cellspacing=2><tr><td align=center> <b><a href="/index.html">ArtemisProject</a></b><td align=center> <b><a href="/asi_index.html">ArtemisSociety</a></b><td align=center> <b><a href="/adb/index.html">ArtemisData Book</a></b><td align=center> <b><a href="/adb/j/index.html">FAQ</a></b><td align=center> <b><a href="/adb/04/index.html">Reference Mission</a></b><td align=center> <b><a href="http://www.tlrc.com/catalog.html">Catalog</a></b></tr></table><hr size="5"><font size=1>Copyright &#169; 1996 Artemis Society International.Updated Mon, June 24, 1996<br>Maintained by <AHREF="MAILTO:simon@eagle.ca">&lt;simon@eagle.ca&gt;</A>.<br>"<a href="/Artemis.html">The Artemis Project</a>"is a trademark of <aHREF="http://www.tlrc.com/Lrc.html">The Lunar ResourcesCompany</a>.</font></body></html>
