prop TC SPTC technical committee member list-->

<h2 align=center>Artemis Data Book</h2>
<h2 align=center>6.7.4.11 Spacecraft Propulsion Technical Committee</h2>
<h2 align=center>Propulsion Tech Committee Membership</h2>
<P><HR><P>

<P>The Spacecraft Propulsion Technical Committee (SPTC) is responsible for
various aspects of rocket science for the Artemis Project. This includes
detailing the <a href="/adb/04/">Reference Mission</a>'s Propulsion needs,
assisting other <a href="/adb/06/07/">Tech Committees</a> and <a
href="/adb/06/08/">Project Teams</a>with propulsion, and working with other
discussion groups. However, working on propulsion aspects of the Reference
Misison is the main focus of the Prop TC.</P>

<UL>
<LI><B>Members</B> - These are people who are actively involved in the
various tasks of the SPTC. They are doing the actual work of the
Propulsion TC itself.
<p>
<LI><B>Reps</B> - Because the activities of the Propulsion Technical
Committee impact many other areas of the <a href="/asi_index.html">Artemis
Society</a>, it is important that strong lines of communication exist
between all Technical Committees. To provide those lines of communication,
we hope to have at least one person from every other Technical Committee
belong to the Propulsion TC as a Rep of that Technical Committee. Reps are
responsible for keeping their Technical Committee informed of activities in
the Propulsion TC and relay requests from their Technical Committee to the
SPTC. Reps may also be active Members of the SPTC if they are active in
both committees.
<p>
<LI><B>Observers</B> - Not considered official members of the SPTC,
observers are people who want to stay informed of what goes on in the
Propulsion TC, usually by being included in the SPTC mailing list or
related information feeds.
</UL>

<p>If you would like to join the Propulsion TC, fill out and submit the
form at the bottom of this page. To see what activities are currently 
going on in the SPTC, look at the <a 
href="propulsion-tc-tasks.html">Propulsion TC Task List</a>. To volunteer 
for one of those tasks, fill out and submit the form on the <a
href="propulsion-tc-tasks.html">Task List</a> page. The current membership
of the SPTC is as follows:</P>

<p><HR><P>

