<html><head><title>6.8.7 SSTO Concept Design Project Team
Membership</title></head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<!-- /adb/06/08/07/ssto-pt.html
 SSTO Concept Design Project Team -->
<!-- Keywords: spacecraft propulsion rocket science engine aeronautical
SSTO Concept Design Project Team member list-->

<h2 align=center>Artemis Data Book</h2>
<h2 align=center>6.8.7 SSTO Concept Design Project Team</h2>
<h2 align=center>SSTO Concept Design PT Membership</h2>
<P><HR><P>

<P>The SSTO Concept Design Project Team is responsible for determining 
and detailing a passenger SSTO conceptual design. This entails designing 
mission architecture, cost, detailed specifications and requirements, and 
other related tasks. Also, it is important to convey the status and 
results of the SSTO Concept Design Project Team to other Technical 
Committees working on related issues, like the Cislunar Space Traffic 
Model, Lunar Tourism, etc.</P>

<UL>
<LI><B>Members</B> - These are people who are actively involved in the
various tasks of the SSTO PT. They are doing the actual work of the
Project Team itself.
<p>
<LI><B>Reps</B> - Because the activities of the SSTO Project Team impact
many other areas of the <a href="/asi_index.html">Artemis Project</a>, it
is important that strong lines of communication exist between all groups.
To provide those lines of communication, we hope to have at least one
person from every relevant Technical Committee belong to the SSTO Project
Team as a Representative of that Technical Committee. Reps are responsible
for keeping their Technical Committee informed of activities in the SSTO
Concept Design Project Team and relay requests from their Technical
Committee to the SSTO team. Reps may also be active Members of the SSTO
Projct Team if they are active in both committees.
<p>
<LI><B>Observers</B> - Not considered official members of the SSTO team,
observers are people who want to stay informed of what goes on in the SSTO
Concept Design Project Team, usually by being included in the SPTC mailing
list or related information feeds.
</UL>

<p>If you would like to join the SSTO Concept Design Project Team, fill out
and submit the form at the bottom of this page. To see what activities are
currently going on in the SSTO Project Team, look at the <a
href="ssto-pt-tasks.html">SSTO PT Task List</a>. To volunteer for one of 
those tasks, fill out and submit the form on the <a
href="ssto-pt-tasks.html">Task List</a> page. The current membership of
the SSTO Concept Design Project Team is as follows:</P>

<p><HR><P>

<h3>Members</h3>
<table border=0 colspan=2>

<tr><td>J. Michael Antoniewicz</td>
<td><a href="mailto:michaela@ncat.edu">
&lt;michaela@ncat.edu&gt;</a></td></tr>

<tr><td>Vlado Barun</td>
<td><a href="mailto:vbarun@andrews.edu">
&lt;vbarun@andrews.edu&gt;</a></td></tr>

<tr><td><a href="http://www.tlrc.com/Bios/bennett.gregory.html">Gregory R.
Bennett</a></td>
<td><a href="mailto:grb@asi.org">
&lt;grb@asi.org&gt;</a></td></tr>

<tr><td>Stan Field</td>
