<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>9.3 "Help" Email Response File</TITLE></HEAD>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<!-- Artemis Data Book -->
<!-- ADB section 9.3 Mailing Lists -->
<!-- file: /adb/09/03/help.html -->
<!-- Keywords: email reponse file autobot  -->
<!-- v 1.0 -->
<h2 align="center">Artemis Data Book</H2>
<h2 align="center">9.3 Mailing Lists</H2>
<h2 align="center">"Help" Email Response File</H2>
<P><HR><P>

<pre>Hi, .

Your HELP command has been received.

To make requests, please send an e-mail containing one or
more lines with the following syntax in the message body to
"list-request" <a
href="mailto:list-request@asi.org">&lt;list-request@asi.org&gt;</a>:

    COMMAND [arguments] [TO|AS reply-address@host.domain]

If [TO|AS reply-address@host.domain] is not specified, the reply
address is extracted from the header of your request message.


These are available commands:
=============================
    JOIN list        - Subscribe to `list'
    SUBSCRIBE list   - Subscribe to `list'
    LEAVE list       - Unsubscribe from `list'
    UNSUBSCRIBE list - Unsubscribe from `list'
    REVIEW list      - List subscribers of `list' [Mailing list only].
    CHANGE address   - Update `address' in all lists.
    WHICH            - Information on what lists you are subscribing to.
    INDEX            - List available packets.
    SEND packet [n]  - Request `packet'; [n] is an optional split size
    SERVERINFO       - Some information about this autoreplyer
    HELP             - This text


`list' can be one of:
    announcements    - Miscellaneous announcments
    asi-ecomm        - Electronic Communication Technical Committee
    asi-web          - Artemis Web Maintainers
    asi-org-local    - Local Artemis Chapters
    art-biz          - Artemis Business Discussions
    art-biz-cdrom    - Artemis CD-ROM Business Discussions
    art-moonbase     - Lunar Outpost Advanced Planning Technical Committee
    art-prop         - Propulsion Technical Committee
    art-ssto         - SSTO Concept Design Team


`packet' can be one of:
    FAQ                    - Artemis project FAQ in text format.
    listmail-announcements - Mail sent to the Announcements list



Some examples:
==============
    SEND item1
    SEND item2 60 TO user@host.domain (Real Name)
    SUBSCRIBE announcements AS user@host.domain (Real Name)
    CHANGE oldaddress@host.domain TO newaddress@host.domain (Real Name)
    SERVERINFO




Downloading information
=======================
    This and that is available via anonymous FTP to <a
href="ftp://ftp.asi.org/">asi.org</a>
    in the directory /pub/path.  Check the INDEX file for details.

    You can also send a message to <a
href="mailto:ftp-request@asi.org">&lt;ftp-request@asi.org&gt;</a>
    containing the words "INDEX /pub/path" in the body.  A
    "HELP" command will give further details on usage.


Addresses
=========
    Board-List@asi.org (Artemis Boards List)
   This list is devoted to Artemis Society board matters

    ectc@asi.org (<a href="/adb/09/01/">Electronic Communications Technical
Committee</a>)
   This list has been renamed asi-ecomm and should no longer be used.
   This list is devoted to <a href="/adb/09/overview.html">Artemis
Electronic Communications</a>
   The activities of the Electronic Communications Technical Committee
   is the current topic.

    <a href="mailto:asi-ecomm@asi.org">asi-ecomm@asi.org</a> (<a
href="/adb/09/01/">Electronic Communications Technical Committee</a>)
   This list is devoted to <a href="/adb/09/overview.html">Artemis
Electronic Communications</a>
   The activities of the Electronic Communications Technical Committee
   is the current topic.

    <a href="mailto:asi-web@asi.org">asi-web@asi.org</a> (Artemis Web
Maintainers)
   This list is devoted to Artemis Web maintenance

    <a href="mailto:asi-org-local@asi.org">asi-org-local@asi.org</a>
(Artemis Local Organizations)
   This list is devoted to local <a
href="/adb/07/local-chapters.html">Artemis chapters</a>
   Getting chapters formed and chartered is the current topic.

    <a href="mailto:art-biz@asi.org">art-biz@asi.org</a> (Artemis Business
Discussions)
   This list is devoted to Artemis business ideas.
   Getting business plans written and products designed is the current topic.

    <a href="mailto:art-biz-cdrom@asi.org">art-biz-cdrom@asi.org</a>
(Artemis CD-ROM Business Discussions)
   This list is devoted to Artemis CD-ROM business discussions.
   Getting <a href="/adb/03/07/cdrom-tasks.html">business plans for CD-ROM
products</a> written and products
   designed is the current topic.

    <a href="mailto:art-moonbase@asi.org">art-moonbase@asi.org</a> (<a
href="/adb/06/07/02/01/">Lunar Outpost Advanced Planning Tech
Committee</a>)
   This list is devoted to the Artemis Lunar Outpost Advanced
   Planning Technical Committee.

    <a href="mailto:art-prop@asi.org">art-prop@asi.org</a> (<a
href="/adb/06/07/04/11/">Propulsion Tech Committee</a>)
   This list is devoted to the Artemis Propulsion Tech Committee.

    <a href="mailto:art-ssto@asi.org">art-ssto@asi.org</a> (<a
href="/adb/06/08/07/">SSTO Concept Design Team</a>)
   This list is devoted to the Artemis SSTO Concept Design Team.

______________________________________________________________________
For help, send an e-mail with HELP body to:    <a
href="mailto:list-request@asi.org">list-request@asi.org</a>
Comments and questions are welcome, use: <a
href="mailto:owner-list-request@asi.org">owner-list-request@asi.org</a>
Artemis Mailing Lists are created and maintained by <a
href="mailto:listmaster@asi.org">&lt;listmaster@asi.org&gt;</a></pre>


