<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>9.4.1 ASI Home Page Design Notes</TITLE></HEAD>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<!-- Artemis Data Book -->
<!-- ADB section 9.4.1 Artemis Project Web Site -->
<!-- file: /adb/09/04/01/home-page-notes.html -->
<!-- v 1.0 -->
<h2 align="center">Artemis Data Book</H2>
<h2 align="center">9.4.1 Artemis Project Web Site</H2>
<h2 align="center">ASI Home Page Design Notes</H2>
<P ALIGN=CENTER><I>Gregory R. Bennett</I></P>
<P><HR><P>


<P>For the new Artemis Project homepage, we're talking about a web site
where the first thing a visitor sees on his screen looks like this...</P>

<PRE>               .--------------------------------------------------.
               |  +-----+-----+-----+-----+-----+-----+-----+     |
               |  | btn | btn | btn | btn | btn | btn | btn |     |
               |  +-----+-----+-----+-----+-----+-----+-----+     |
               |  | btn |  Welcome to . . .                       |
               |  +-----+                                         |
               |  | btn |  T h e   A r t e m i s  P r o j e c t   |
               |  +-----+                                         |
               |  | btn |  We're going to the moon,               |
               |  +-----+           and you can come, too!        |
               |  | btn |                                         |
               |  +-----+                                         |
               |  | btn |                                         |
               |  +-----+                                         |
               |  | btn |                                         |
               |  +-----+                                         |
               |  | btn |                                         |
               |  +-----+  fine print fine print fine print       |
                --------------------------------------------------</PRE>


<P>...and the logic the user will experience is that that site has two
sides: one for learning about the project, and one for the nitty-gritty
details. Like this...</P>


<PRE>                                -----------------
                               |                 |
                               |  Main Entrance  |
                               |                 |
                                -----------------
                                       |
                        -----------------------------
                       |                             |
             --------------------          --------------------
            |                    |        |                    |
            |        Tour        |        | Artemis Data Book  |
            |                    |        |                    |
             --------------------          --------------------
                  |                                  |
             -----------                    -------------------
            |1          | Designed         |         |         |
            |           | for            -----     -----     -----
             -----------  linear        |  |  |   |  |  |   |  |  |
                  |       tour,
             -----------  with          Same format we're now using;
            |2          | random        designed for random access
            |           | access        via indexes, outlines,
             -----------  via           directories, and search
                  |       buttons.      engines.
             -----------
            |3          | Tutorial
            |           | documents
             -----------  use same
                  |       standard
             -----------  layout as
            |4          | the main
            |           | entrance.
             -----------
                  |
             -----------
            |5          |
            |           |
             -----------</PRE>

<P>The really significant point here is that all those tour pages would
have the same format as the main entrance. Note that the body of those
tour pages really should be part of the <a href="/adb/">Artemis Data
Book</a>. There is no reason why the Tour can't access pages stored in the
Data Book's structure; and lots of reasons why it should do so. All this
will be transparent to the visitor, unless he likes to study URL's as he
surfs the waves through the site.</P>

<P>Each tour page will necessarily be very short to avoid scrolling,
making just one or two major points about the project. Graphics on these
pages will be small, with limited screen real estate available.</P>

<P>One recommendation for the graphical design for the Tour: put forward 
and backward buttons, obviously arrows, centered on the bottom of the 
screen, with no other clutter near them. Set up the tour so that a 
visitor can click through the whole tour without even moving his mouse.</P>


