<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>9.8. Real-time Meetings</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<!-- Artemis Data Book -->
<!-- ADB section 9.8. Real-time Meetings -->
<!-- file: /adb/09/08/clients.html -->
<!-- v 1.0 -->
<H2 ALIGN="center">Artemis Data Book</H2>
<H2 ALIGN="center">9.8. Real-time Meetings</H2>
<H2 ALIGN="center">IRC Client Software</H2>
<P><I></I></P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER">Brian Cesar</P>
<P></P>
<HR>
<P>
Basically, the term &quot;IRC client software&quot; simply refers
to the particular software package that enables your system to connect to and
use an IRC network. If you are not familiar with IRC, please see the <a
href="http://www.irchelp.org/irchelp/altircfaq.txt">Alternative IRC FAQ
page</A>.
<BR><BR>Each piece of client software has several common features and
enable a user to :
<BR>
</P>
<OL type="A">
<LI>Connect to an existing IRC network
<LI>Chat with other IRC users by typing conversations on your computer
screen
<LI>Perform file transfers to other IRC users
</OL>
<P>Other common features are nickname changing, private (DCC) chat, and
others too numerous to mention here. Please see the <a
href="http://www.irchelp.org/irchelp/altircfaq.txt">Alternative IRC FAQ</A>
page or your software's help files for further information.
<BR>
</P>
<P>
<b>Installation:</b><BR>
Each package installs differently, so no attempt will be made to list
these instructions on this page. PLEASE NOTE: installation and help  files are
available for each software package at the site listed. Please download both the
program itself and any help files along  with it! The system administrator of
ASI IRC cannot possibly keep up  with it all, so please be an informed user and
read your help files !
<BR>
</P>
<HR>
<P><A NAME="IRC-Client"></A>
<h3>Freeware/Shareware IRC Client Software Commonly Available for Download</h3>
<i>(Listed by Operating System)</i>
</P>
<UL>
