<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">

<h2 align=center>September 1996 ECTC IRC Meeting Transcript</h2>

On Sunday, September 1, 1996 at 7:00 pm EST the Artemis Electronic Communications Technical Committee held their first Internet Relay Chat (IRC) meeting.  The meeting was held on the ASI IRC server on atlantis.io.com using channel #ectc.  The meeting was attended by the following people:
<p>
Randall Severy (Severy)<br>
Tim Cadell (TimCadell)<br>
David Brummel (dbrummel)<br>
Candace Dicks (cdb-home)<br>
Brad Ackerman (Ackerman)<br>
<p>
The following is a transcript of the conversation that occurred during the meeting.  There were some occasional dropped network connections that disconnected some participants from time to time during the meeting.  References to the network disconnects and some personal conversation not related to the business of the meeting have been edited out of the transcript.
<p>
<b><i>Session Start: Sun Sep 01 18:31:33 1996</i></b>
<br><b><i>*** TimCadell (~tmp@206.149.221.68) has joined #ectc</i></b>
<br><b>&lt;TimCadell&gt;</b> Hey, I'm here.  You all there?
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Hi, Tim!
<br><b>&lt;TimCadell&gt;</b> Perfect timing.  I walked into the 
Internet Lounge here at World Con...
<br><b>&lt;TimCadell&gt;</b> and it's the right time.
<br><b><i>*** dbrummel (me@dialup-01-001.houston.io.com) has joined #ectc</i></b>
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Hi, David!
<br><b>&lt;TimCadell&gt;</b> Hi, David.
<br><b>&lt;dbrummel&gt;</b> Hi, Randall, Tim
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Welcome to our little gathering!
<br><b><i>*** cdb-home (~cdb@tam-fl1-14.ix.netcom.com) has joined #ectc</i></b>
<br><b>&lt;cdb-home&gt;</b> This is Candace...I have a couple of 
questions about 3D mailing list  Should I ask 
now?
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Hi, Candace!
<br><b>&lt;TimCadell&gt;</b> Hi, Candace.  Nice to meet you.
<br><b>&lt;cdb-home&gt;</b> I'm trying to figure out what the 3D 
Tech Comm mailing list name is supposed to be. 
Greg suggested art-biz-graphics?
<br><b>&lt;cdb-home&gt;</b> Tim..  I'd like to ask questions for a 
few min after the meeting.
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Candace, that name sounds fine with me
<br><b>&lt;TimCadell&gt;</b> Great, Candace.  As long as they let me 
sit here.  I'm at the WorldCon and there's a 
one-hour limit, but unless they /kick me, that's 
great.
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Officially, it's up to Greg to establish 
the list names and which section in the ADB they 
go in
<br><b>&lt;cdb-home&gt;</b> About Help Desk Task #6, Randall...maybe 
you can stay too?
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Yep, I'm planning to stick around until 9 
pm EST
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> In any case, in the interests of keeping 
to the schedule, I had planned to spend the first 
fifteen minutes or so in welcoming everyone and 
making sure everyone knew their way around the 
IRC environment
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Does everyone here know everyone else?
<br><b>&lt;cdb-home&gt;</b> Randall, I'll need to be the mailing 
list person for the 3D til the end of 96, or 
Craig finds someone else. That's my limit for 
3D.
<br><b>&lt;TimCadell&gt;</b> At least by reading email.  Hi, 
everyone.
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Ok, Candace, it's easy enough to change 
the ownership of a list
<br><b>&lt;dbrummel&gt;</b> I *think* I've seen most of these names 
in .sigs :)
<br><b>&lt;cdb-home&gt;</b> Hi..This is Candace...I'm the Office of Space 
Flight Tech Council Administrator.
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> If anyone doesn't know someone else, don't hesitate 
to ask!
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Did anyone have any trouble finding this place?
<br><b>&lt;TimCadell&gt;</b> Nope, just read my email.
<br><b>&lt;dbrummel&gt;</b> Not once I remembered the port number (a bit 
non-standard, that) :)
<br><b>&lt;cdb-home&gt;</b> No trouble at all this time. It payed to be a 
little familiar from last weekend's artemis chat.
<br><b>&lt;Ackerman&gt;</b> No more trouble than downloading an IRC client -- 
the public labs here don't have one installed.  (just typed 
in the URL to d/l one.)
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Kindof, I used that port because that's the one they 
used on DALnet for the BBC IRC conference
<br><b>&lt;TimCadell&gt;</b> Hmmm.  Strange, I too had to change the default in 
mIRC, wrong port.
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> I went back and forth between 6667 and 7000 and ended 
up with 7000 for that reason
<br><b>&lt;dbrummel&gt;</b> 7000 does give us a bit more security from 
wandering strangers
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> If it makes extra work for people we might want to 
switch back to 6667 for future meetings
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Hmm, good point, David, that's something to keep in 
mind
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Is everyone here comfortable with the IRC 
environment?  Any questions about it?
<br><b>&lt;TimCadell&gt;</b> Of course, you can always just close the meeting 
without invitations, right?  But 7000's fine with me.
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Yeah, if I had stayed Op I could have made this a 
private channel
<br><b>&lt;cdb-home&gt;</b> My only problem was getting access to service 
provider itself...It took about 15 min to log in.
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Ouch!
<br><b>&lt;dbrummel&gt;</b> comfy-cozy here
<br><b>&lt;TimCadell&gt;</b> Not a problem today.
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Ok, well, I'll give things another few minutes to see 
if anyone else shows up and then we'll get started
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Ok, as it is now 15 minutes into the meeting, I guess 
it's time to get started
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> I had hoped to have a few more people show up, but 
five isn't bad for our first time
<br><b>&lt;TimCadell&gt;</b> Ready.
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> I had planned to give an update on the ASI domain 
move at this point, but I think I covered most of that in 
recent posts to artemis-list
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Basically, the web site and mailing lists are back in 
operation
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> But the web site is on autopilot as it seems that 
Dana is the only one with permissions to update the files
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> With Dana away at Worldcon, we haven't been able to 
make much progress in that area
<br><i>* TimCadell chuckles</i>
<br><b>&lt;cdb-home&gt;</b> I've had trouble with ssdgwy.mdc.com members being 
undeliverable for asi-osf-leads!!!
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> The mailing lists are running, but the new digest 
features are giving us some problems
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Hmm, are those address with pound signs in them, 
Candace?
<br><b>&lt;cdb-home&gt;</b> yes they have # signs
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Yep, we ran into that with the board-list list as 
well
<br><b>&lt;TimCadell&gt;</b> Software doesn't like that?
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> It seems that Majordomo treats everything after a # 
sign as a comment and strips off the rest of the address!
<br><b>&lt;TimCadell&gt;</b> Have you tried escaping the #?  Something like \#  
?
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> We've tried everything we can think of to work around 
that and even the Majordomo expert at IO is baffled
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Hmm, haven't tried \#, I'll give that a try later
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> I've asked Greg to ask some folks at MDC because they 
all use # signs and they must have run into this before
<br><b>&lt;cdb-home&gt;</b> It also hiccups on the & sign in Dave Anderson's 
email.
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> But I haven't heard back from him yet on this issue
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> An "&" sign in an e-mail address?  I'm not surprised 
it hiccups!
<br><b>&lt;TimCadell&gt;</b> Is Majordomo a shell program?
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Ok, I'll look into that as well
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> I believe Majordomo passes the addresses as 
parameters to sendmail
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> That may be why this is happening
<br><b>&lt;cdb-home&gt;</b> I talked to greg once...It seems he never has 
problems when he is a work,  but I always have problems!
<br><b>&lt;TimCadell&gt;</b> Yup.  You should be able to escape them, even the 
'&'.
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Majordomo itself is a Perl program, but lets other 
programs do most of the work
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Good idea, I'll try the shell escapes
<br><b>&lt;TimCadell&gt;</b> You might have to try multiples.  I'm not sure at 
what point it'll apply the escapes.
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Ouch, that could be a pain because it often takes 
Majordomo several hours to respond to requests!
<br><b>&lt;cdb-home&gt;</b> I tried escaping the & sign when we were on other 
server . It didn't work. Should I try again , or wait til 
you check it out.
<br><b>&lt;TimCadell&gt;</b> Randall -> Try sending different letters to 
different addresses; work the problem in paralle.
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> The other server had a completely different mail 
program, so it probably would have handled it completely 
differently
<br><b>&lt;cdb-home&gt;</b> Ah ...O.K.
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Yep, I'll try that Tim, I have a test mailing list 
for just that purpose
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Candace, if you can give me the address, I'll test it 
out at the same time I work on the # sign problem
<br><b>&lt;cdb-home&gt;</b> I'll email them to you right after meeting...that 
O.K?
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Yep, that's fine
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> So the remaining action items from the ASI domain 
move are:
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> 1) Fix the permissions on the web site (owner=Dana)
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> 2) Solve the problems with # and & characters in 
mailing list addresses (owner=Randall)
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> and 3) fix archive and digest issues with mailing 
lists (owner=Randal)
<br><b>&lt;cdb-home&gt;</b> Oh...the & problem. Here is the given address :  
anderson#d#dave_#l#gn&c#r#@ssdgwy.mdc.com    that is an l 
after dave_#
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Sheesh, they have complicated addresses at MDC!
<br><b>&lt;TimCadell&gt;</b> You're kidding! Wow, what an address.
<br><b>&lt;cdb-home&gt;</b> Dave's *is* the worst.
<br><b>&lt;TimCadell&gt;</b> McDonnell Douglas?
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Yep
<br><b>&lt;Ackerman&gt;</b> Do they put the whole thing on business cards?
<br><i>* TimCadell chuckles.</i>
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> I sometimes wonder the same thing!
<br><b>&lt;TimCadell&gt;</b> Actually, I've seen longer at Taco Bell, but 
still...  Oi.
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> I'm starting to see a lot of MDC people set up 
aliases that don't include the # signs
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Don't even get me started about my old UUCP 
addresses!
<br><b>&lt;cdb-home&gt;</b> Greg set up...or Randall did... an asi.org address 
for some of them. But since it still goes to MDC.....Well, 
you get the idea. It Poofs!
<br><b>&lt;TimCadell&gt;</b> I remember.  Lots of bangs.
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Ok, unless there are any questions about the ASI 
domain move, let's move on to the status of ECTC projects
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Yeah, I set up a couple of asi.org aliases for folks 
at MDC
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Yep, Tim, at one point I think I had 5 or 6 bangs in 
my address!
<br><b>&lt;cdb-home&gt;</b> O.K. I'm ready for next topic (grin)
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Since it's first on the list, we might as well start 
with Help Desk task #6 ;-)
<br><b>&lt;cdb-home&gt;</b> what list?
<br><b>&lt;TimCadell&gt;</b> Top of the list, huh?  Where to begin.
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Candace, I need to first apologize about not getting 
back to you earlier about the sample interview you put 
together
<br><b>&lt;dbrummel&gt;</b> What's the URL for the list?
<br><b>&lt;cdb-home&gt;</b> apology accepted.
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> With the asi.org move and starting up this new 
company, those messages ended up at the bottom of the pile
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> The ECTC task list is at http://www.asi.org/adb/09/01/
ectc_tasks.html
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> One thing I've been hoping to do about that interview 
is to track down who first suggested it
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> It was suggested at Artemis '96 and I think it was 
either Nanci or Ian who first mentioned it
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Actually, David, you might remember, I think you were 
in on that discussion, if I remember correctly?
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Whoever suggested it had some good ideas for the 
types of questions to ask
<br><b>&lt;cdb-home&gt;</b> Oh,  O.K. Did I come close?
<br><b>&lt;dbrummel&gt;</b> Remember what?
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Well, not quite, and that was why I was trying to 
find out the original suggestions
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Your list was more of a general biographical and 
categorical list
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> David, were you around when either Nanci or Ian and I 
discussed the new volunteer interview pages?
<br><b>&lt;cdb-home&gt;</b> I'll still volunteer to do the HTML of the pages.
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> The ideas either Nanci or Ian proposed revolved 
around more of a real "interview" as opposed to 
"census-type" stuff
<br><b>&lt;TimCadell&gt;</b> I read your pages, Candace.  Better HTML, or at 
least higher, than what I can write so far.
<br><b>&lt;dbrummel&gt;</b> Randall, sorry, can't recall too many specific 
discussions from that weekend (overload)
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Sure, Candace, you can do whatever parts of it you 
want!
<br><b>&lt;TimCadell&gt;</b> So, the program would start somewhere and go 
different directions depending on answers?
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Not really, since you can't easily change HTML forms 
dynamically as you go along
<br><b>&lt;cdb-home&gt;</b> Just send me the questions....and the flowchart.
<br><b>&lt;TimCadell&gt;</b> If I understand the comments in earlier mail, the 
problem is the lack of a flowchart, yes?
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> But after asking all of the questions, a CGI script 
would look up matches to those answers in a table somewhere 
and come up with recommendations for areas of the Artemis 
Project to volunteer
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> I don't have the questions, Candace, that's part of 
the problem! ;-)
<br><b>&lt;cdb-home&gt;</b> General ideas...I could work on wording.
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Some of the suggestions I remember from Artemis '96 
were things like "what interests you about space?", "how 
much do you know about the Internet?"
<br><i>* Severy racks his memory trying to dredge up these things</i>
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> "How much time would you be interested in devoting to 
the Artemis Project?"
<br><b>&lt;TimCadell&gt;</b> Are they going to answer in English?  Tricky 
programming for a CGI script!
<br><b>&lt;cdb-home&gt;</b> Is it like Planetary Society Mailing?
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> "Are you interested in leading a team of people?"  -- 
which might steer people to be a committee chair
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> No, Tim, what we had in mind was a multiple-choice 
answer
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> For some of the answers, there might be a multiple 
choice based on ranges
<br><b>&lt;TimCadell&gt;</b> Hmmm.  So each committee would submit something 
that described someone they'd want working with them...
<br><b>&lt;TimCadell&gt;</b> and we'd make a program that steered people that 
match to the committees looking for them?
