<br><b>&lt;dbrummel&gt;</b> Randall,  all the services worth spit give users 
full inet access, so I don't see any need for special 
areas on them.
<br><b>&lt;TimCadell&gt;</b> A lot of BBS's are doing that, too, aren't they?
<br><b>&lt;Ackerman&gt;</b> But many have active space discussion forums 
anyhow.
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Yeah, there are still some efforts to post Artemis 
material in specific places, but the efforts to establish 
links with the mailing lists have definitely faded away
<br><b>&lt;dbrummel&gt;</b> Tim, those that can afford a full-time connection. 
(which I can't :(  )
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> The mailing list link to GEnie is about to die when 
my GEnie account gets cancelled
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> David, any news to report on the BBS front?
<br><b>&lt;TimCadell&gt;</b> Well, for just newsgroups, you could supply a 
partial connection without full-time, couldn't you?
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> You had some questions a few months back about UUCP 
connections, are there still issues there?
<br><b>&lt;dbrummel&gt;</b> Tim, yes, but I can't support much traffic.
<br><b>&lt;dbrummel&gt;</b> Randall, last I talked with IO, they were 
unwilling to setup UUCP due to lack of demand.
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Hmm, sounds like IO!
<br><b>&lt;TimCadell&gt;</b> Hmmm...
<br><b>&lt;dbrummel&gt;</b> I have been investigating other means of gating 
news into my BBS and have found acouple of ways to do this 
over a PPP link.
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Are you still doing your link part-time?
<br><b>&lt;Ackerman&gt;</b> NNTP.
<br><b>&lt;dbrummel&gt;</b> I'm gating mail via my UUCP link w/Holonet and 
news via PPP from IO
<br><b>&lt;TimCadell&gt;</b> Should work.  I've read news that way, once with 
a Perl script.
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> How is that working, David?
<br><b>&lt;dbrummel&gt;</b> Holonet still serves my domain, so they will 
continue to do my mail until I move the domain elsewhere.
<br><b>&lt;dbrummel&gt;</b> News I'm bringing down with a pgm called souper, 
and have other s/w which can gate it into the BBS.
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Ok, David, are there any issues that need resolved 
or any action items left around?
<br><b>&lt;TimCadell&gt;</b> I need to get going.  They need the computer I'm 
on.
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Oops, can we wrap this up quickly?
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> How much time do you have left, Tim?
<br><b>&lt;TimCadell&gt;</b> About a minute, i told him.
<br><b>&lt;dbrummel&gt;</b> The only issues for me are 1) how much traffic 
will there be and 2) how much interest from Fido?
<br><b>&lt;TimCadell&gt;</b> They have a line.
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> I can imagine, Tim!
<br><b>&lt;TimCadell&gt;</b> It's not long, but it's impatient.  And they've 
been very nice to setup this free service.  20 computers 
over ISDN.
<br><b>&lt;Ackerman&gt;</b> Lines have been on and off here, but I haven't 
drawn much attention.  (Lines a mile long in the cafeteria 
upstairs. :( )
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Ok, when you next get a chance, I'd be interested in 
any feedback you have on this meeting
<br><b>&lt;dbrummel&gt;</b> So far, I haven't found any Fido echoes where we 
might troll for interest :(
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> i.e., what worked and what didn't work, and 
suggestings for improving future meetings
<br><b>&lt;TimCadell&gt;</b> Randall -> Okay, otherwise, I consider it pretty 
good excepting IRC's problems.
<br><b>&lt;TimCadell&gt;</b> You got it.
<br><b>&lt;TimCadell&gt;</b> See you all later!
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Yeah, I'll drop IO a line about the disconnections 
and see if they know anything about them
<br><i>* Severy waves goodbye to Tim</i>
<br><b>&lt;Ackerman&gt;</b> Same opinions as Tim.
<br><b><i>*** TimCadell has quit IRC (Leaving)</i></b>
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> David, what do you mean by that?
<br><b>&lt;dbrummel&gt;</b> Randall, mean by which?
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> By not finding any Fido echos
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Is there no interest in propogating the Artemis 
mailing lists through Fido?
<br><b>&lt;dbrummel&gt;</b> Ah.  Last I checked the Fido echo list, there did 
not seem to be any echoes on space-ralted topics, other 
than specific sci-fi echoes (Trek, Star Wars, et al).
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Hmm, is it worth proposing an Artemis echo?
<br><b>&lt;dbrummel&gt;</b> I've never had *any* inquiries about picking up 
the maillists.
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Hmm, do other people even know about them?
<br><b>&lt;Ackerman&gt;</b> If there aren't any space echoes, then how about 
starting SPACE?
<br><b>&lt;dbrummel&gt;</b> We'd need to generate enough interest to get 
several Fido regions to request an echo, after having a 
thriving echo in the local region.
<br><b>&lt;dbrummel&gt;</b> It might be doen, but more and more people are 
moving to the i'net...
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> I was wondering about that aspect of it...
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Ok, in the interest of wrapping this meeting up, 
let's move on to the next section
<br><b>&lt;dbrummel&gt;</b> The local region has been bleeding nodes like a 
major artery had been cut.
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Which is, appropriately enough, "Real-time Meetings"
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Brad, how much have you been helping Brian with the 
IRC stuff?
<br><b>&lt;Ackerman&gt;</b> We haven't gotten together in a few weeks -- he 
pretty much took care of the IRC procedure guide.
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Ok, we've definitely made a lot of progress on the 
IRC stuff this month!
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> I think the next phase there is to refine the 
procedure guide based on the experiences we are starting to 
have, both with the BBC IRC conference and this meeting
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> We may want to start investigating a few related 
things
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> The subject of web interfaces to IRC came up in the 
BBC conference
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> It might be worth exploring setting up a web page on 
the ASI site that allows people to participate in these 
meetings
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Since some people might have trouble setting up an 
IRC client
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> There are also non-IRC chat servers that we might 
want to investigate
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Especially if the IRC environment remains as 
unstable as we've seen the two times we've used it
<br><b>&lt;dbrummel&gt;</b> Do you have a candidate list?
<br><b>&lt;Ackerman&gt;</b> The best way to interface WWW with IRC would 
probably be a Java-based IRC client.
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Nope, I printed some web pages on some when I 
stumbled on them months ago but they are buried under large 
piles of paper ;-)
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Yeah, a Java applet version of an IRC client was 
mentioned in the BBC conference, I have a URL for one 
floating around here somewhere
<br><b>&lt;dbrummel&gt;</b> If you find those pages, I could investigate some 
of the other chatware.
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Ahh, here it is:
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> http://webx.best.com/~kbs/irctst/jirc.html
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> For basic chat servers, I found most of them off the 
Yahoo "Chatting" pages
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> For basic chat servers, I found most of them off the 
Yahoo "Chatting" pages
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Go to Yahoo, select the Internet link and go into 
the "Chatting" area
<br><b>&lt;dbrummel&gt;</b> Gotcha
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> There is a subpage for IRC, but there is also a list 
of lots of other chat servers
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Most of them are commercial and so would cost too 
much for us, but there were a couple of freeware ones
<br><b>&lt;dbrummel&gt;</b>mel> OK.  I'll see what I can find out.  Due date?
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Brad, would you be interested in investigating the 
Java client?
<br><b>&lt;Ackerman&gt;</b> Sure.
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Hmm, I don't know, David, end of the month?
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> We might want to use IRC some more to see how it 
works before we make any major moves towards something else
<br><b>&lt;Ackerman&gt;</b> Esp. if we can get those netsplits down.
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> But it would be worth experimenting with other 
options, if they look intriguing
<br><b>&lt;dbrummel&gt;</b> Agreed
<br><b>&lt;Ackerman&gt;</b> Just make sure that whatever we do can be accessed 
via telnet.
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Hmm, many of the chat servers seemed to be 
web-based, so I have a feeling telnet wouldn't work
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Is telnet access an important requirement?
<br><b>&lt;Ackerman&gt;</b> Web-based would probably be OK.  My primary 
concern is that the chat can be accessed without 
proprietary (and possibly platform-specific) software.
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> That's true, we've seen enough platform arguments 
around here to know we can't stick with a single platform!
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Anyway, it sounds like we have enough to work on in 
this area, ready for the next section?
<br><b>&lt;dbrummel&gt;</b> Hey! I resemble that remark!  :)  :)
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> The last section is aptly named "Miscellaneous"
<br><b>&lt;dbrummel&gt;</b> There's more?!?!?
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> I think the only item in that section that involves 
any of us is the credit card stuff
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Brad, I've been thinking a bit about that area in 
light of some of the recent discussions in the ASI board
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> There seems to be a general plan to leave the sales 
activities to LRC and leave ASI out of the sales business
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> If that's the case, I'm not sure there would be any 
use for a credit card ordering system for ASI
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> There definitely is such a need for LRC, so it's not 
like the work doesn't need to be done
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> But I'm thinking we may need to move those efforts 
under the LRC umbrella
<br><b>&lt;dbrummel&gt;</b> I think IO just installed a secure server (check 
the IO Revealed page)
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Brad, you may want to contact Greg and Dana about 
this area
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> I know that Dana was planning to look into credit 
card ordering stuff for the LRC catalog, so there's no 
reason to duplicate efforts in that area
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> David, yeah, I saw that note as well, I'm not sure 
how that will impact us
<br><b>&lt;Ackerman&gt;</b> Agreed.  I'll have to get in touch with them.
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> I'll drop Greg a note as well to see what he things 
should be done in this area
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> things = thinks
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> And on that note, I believe we have finally finished 
the ECTC task list!
<br><b>&lt;Ackerman&gt;</b> Credit card processing is one of the trickier 
bits, especially if we handle the whole arrangement 
ourselves.
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Yep, they are definitely going to have to figure all 
of that out for the LRC catalog, so they could probably use 
the help
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> So, any closing thoughts before we wrap up this 
meeting?
<br><b>&lt;dbrummel&gt;</b> none here
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Are there ways in which this meeting should have 
been organized differently?
<br><b>&lt;Ackerman&gt;</b> Probably off-topic, but I can't wait until this 
computer lab is upgraded to PowerPC. :)
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> So as to better adapt to the IRC environment?
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> What's the lab running now?
<br><b>&lt;Ackerman&gt;</b> Mac IIci's.
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Ouch, those probably seem pretty slow these days!
<br><b>&lt;Ackerman&gt;</b> The RevRdist hard drive virginization takes 5-10 
minutes.
<br><b>&lt;dbrummel&gt;</b> Was the agenda posted on the Web?  I'm running 
Win95 right now, but my dobharchu.org e-mail is under OS/2 
and unaccessable. :(
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> The agenda was posted in an e-mail message yesterday
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> I should have posted it earlier, and that's probably 
why the attendence wasn't larger
<br><b>&lt;dbrummel&gt;</b> Right.  And I can't get to it.  A copy on the Web 
would be nice.
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> I'll make sure I give more advance notice next time, 
things just got too busy the last few days...
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Good idea, I'll make sure future info is available 
on the web
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Speaking of the web, there was some discussion last 
week about making edited transcripts of these sessions 
available for those who couldn't make it
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Do either of you feel strongly either way about 
publishing what we've said here?
<br><b>&lt;dbrummel&gt;</b> Were you able to log all of this through all the 
drops?
<br><b>&lt;Ackerman&gt;</b> Nope -- what I've said is ok for publication.
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Yep, I believe so, I'll have to double-check but I 
have logging turned on automatically
<br><b>&lt;dbrummel&gt;</b> I have no problems with posting this, assuming you 
got it all :)
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> and I think mIRC just appends to the log files
<br><b>&lt;Ackerman&gt;</b> The multiple netsplits might merit some clipping.
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Ok, I should have made a public statement in the 
beginning about publishing a transcript
<br><b>&lt;dbrummel&gt;</b> OK.  I just d/l'd mIRC this afternoon, so I 
haven't wrung out all the features, yet :)
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> and I'll have to remember that for next time, so I 
won't have to get permissions retroactively
<br><b>&lt;Ackerman&gt;</b> So noted.
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Yeah, I'm going to edit out the netsplits and other 
chit-chat
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Yep, I just checked the log file and everything's in 
there
<br><b>&lt;dbrummel&gt;</b> kewl
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Ok, anything else to discuss or are we all talked 
out?
<br><b>&lt;dbrummel&gt;</b> my fingers are worn to nubs <g>
<br><b>&lt;Ackerman&gt;</b> We've covered just about everything -- I've got 
about 20 minutes to grab dinner before the cafeteria 
closes.
<br><i>* Severy grins</i>
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> That's the best reason to wrap this up that I've 
heard so far!
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Well, it's been great talking to you both!
<br><b>&lt;dbrummel&gt;</b> 'til next time...
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> And I'm looking forward to next month's meeting, 
hopefully we'll get more people here then
<br><b>&lt;Ackerman&gt;</b> aufwiedersehen...
<br><b>&lt;dbrummel&gt;</b> slan!
<br><i>* Severy waves goodbye to Brad and David</i>
<br><i>* Ackerman waves</i>
<br><i>* dbrummel ducks out the door, with a wave</i>
<br><b><i>*** Ackerman has quit IRC (So long, and thanks for all the 
fish.)</i></b>
<br><b><i>*** dbrummel has quit IRC (Leaving)</i></b>
<br><b><i>Session Close: Sun Sep 01 21:51:52 1996</i></b>
