<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">

<h2 align=center>October 1996 ECTC IRC Meeting Transcript</h2>

On Sunday, October 6, 1996 at 7:00 pm EST the Artemis Electronic Communications Technical Committee held their second Internet Relay Chat (IRC) meeting.  The meeting was held on the ASI IRC server on atlantis.io.com using channel #ectc.  The meeting was attended by the following people:
<p>
Randall Severy (Severy)<br>
Candace Dicks (cdb-home)<br>
Brad Ackerman (BradA)<br>
David Brummel (DavidB)<br>
Brian Cesar (Brian_C)<br>
<p>
The following is a transcript of the conversation that occurred during the meeting.  There were some occasional dropped network connections that disconnected some participants from time to time during the meeting.  References to the network disconnects and some personal conversation not related to the business of the meeting have been edited out of the transcript.
<p>
<b><i>Session Start: Sun Oct 06 19:00:11 1996</i></b>
<br><b><i>*** cdb-home (~cdb@206.214.117.80) has joined #ectc</i></b>
<br><b>&lt;cdb-home&gt;</b> I got here after all!
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Hi, Candace!
<br><b><i>*** BradA (bsa3@SBY10.CIT.CORNELL.EDU) has joined #ectc</i></b>
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Hi, Brad!
<br><b>&lt;cdb-home&gt;</b> Hello again!
<br><i>* Severy waves to Candace</i>
<br><b>&lt;BradA&gt;</b> `allo.
<br><b>&lt;cdb-home&gt;</b> Hiya
<br><b><i>*** DavidB (~dbrummel@dialup-01-012.houston.io.com) has joined #ectc</i></b>
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Hi, David!
<br><b>&lt;DavidB&gt;</b> hello
<br><b>&lt;cdb-home&gt;</b> Hi
<br><b>&lt;BradA&gt;</b> Hello DavidB, welcome to #ectc
<br><b>&lt;cdb-home&gt;</b> I forgot to get in touch with Morris M. My netcom 
mailbox server hiccuped again.
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Well, Morris received the announcement of this 
meeting, so he might show up
<br><b>&lt;cdb-home&gt;</b> Hope so.
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Although so far it looks like just us regulars!
<br><b>&lt;cdb-home&gt;</b> You said you were out of the email loop for a few 
days. Did ya see my "Artemis Convention Carole"?
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Yep, I saw your carole!
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Actually, I don't think I was out of the email loop, 
just that strange things are going on with the asi.org 
mailing lists
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> I got a message from art-biz this afternoon, but 
that was the first message I saw from any of the asi.org 
lists since Thursday
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> I sent out the announcement for this meeting to 
asi-ecomm three times and I never saw the message come back
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> That's why I ended up sending it individually to 
everyone subscribed to the asi-ecomm list
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Did any of you see any of the announcements to 
asi-ecomm, or did you only get the one message I sent to 
the individual addresses?
<br><b>&lt;DavidB&gt;</b> I only got the announcement you sent on Sat.
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> I was afraid of that, I'm starting to wonder if it 
was only the asi-ecomm list that is goofed up
<br><b>&lt;cdb-home&gt;</b> Only the one sent to individual members (sat) and 
the preview on Sept 29.
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Did anyone here send any messages to any of the 
lists since this past Thursday?
<br><b>&lt;BradA&gt;</b> I think only the individual member one got to me.
<br><b>&lt;cdb-home&gt;</b> I'm checking my mailbox...be right back.
<br><b>&lt;DavidB&gt;</b> ecomm is the only asi.org list i'm on - nothing 
between thurs. & sat.
<br><b><i>*** Brian_C (~bcesar@dial-alb1-7.surfsouth.com) has joined #ectc</i></b>
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Hi, Brian!
<br><b>&lt;cdb-home&gt;</b> Tried checking my mailbox...If I had mailing list 
postings, I deleted them. Hmmmm. P.S. Hi Brian.
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Does anyone need introductions around here?
<br><b>&lt;Brian_C&gt;</b> good evening all! May be in&out... connecting on 
the sly from worw :)
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Ok, I guess that's enough time to collect any late 
arrivals, I guess it's time to start...
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> I think all of you know me, BradA is Brad Ackerman, 
Brian_C is Brian Cesar,...
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> cdb-home is Candace Dicks Bartleson, and DavidB is 
David Brummel
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Does everyone know their way around IRC?  Any 
initial questions on how this all works?
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Since everyone here except Brian was here last 
month, Brian, let me give you a few warnings about what 
might happen
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Last month we had a recurring problem with dropped 
Internet connections that disconnected various people from 
time to time
<br><b>&lt;cdb-home&gt;</b> Yes I'm ok.
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> So far tonight things look good
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> If I'm dropped, I'll lose the Op priveleges, but 
since this is a private meeting I'm not too worried about that
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> If anyone is dropped, just reconnect as soon as you 
can and we'll pick up where we left off
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> So, on that note, let's move on to the third item on 
the agenda: Review current project status
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Just like last month I'm a little tardy on finishing 
the monthly status report
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> I promised myself I'd have it out before this 
meeting so I wouldn't have to waste time reviewing the current status
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> But as often happens, events did not quite work out 
that way...
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> So, starting with the first section of the ECTC task 
list: Help Desk
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> I think the only task in that section that involves 
people here is the volunteer interview
<br><b>&lt;Severy&gt;</b> Candace, did I get a status report from you this 
month?
