<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>M.2.6 Lunar Orbiter Missions Summary</TITLE></HEAD><body bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><!-- Artemis Data Book --><!-- ADB section M.2.6 Lunar Orbiter --><!-- file: /adb/m/02/06/mission-summary.html --><!-- v 1.0 --><h2 align="center">Artemis Data Book</H2><h2 align="center">M.2.6 Lunar Orbiter</H2><h2 align="center">Lunar Orbiter Missions Summary</H2><P ALIGN=CENTER><I>Larry Klaes</I></P><P><HR><P><P>LUNAR ORBITER (LUNAR SURFACE PHOTOGRAPHY)</P><P>LUNAR ORBITER 1 through 5 were designed to orbit the Moon and image    various sites being studied as landing areas for the manned APOLLO    missions of 1969-1972. The probes also contributed greatly to our    understanding of lunar surface features, particularly the lunar farside.    All five probes of the series, launched from 1966 to 1967, were    essentially successful in their missions. They were the first U.S.    probes to orbit the Moon. All LOs were eventually crashed into the lunar    surface to avoid interference with the manned <ahref="/adb/m/02/07/">APOLLO</a> missions</a>.</p><!-- Nav Bar --><hr size="5"><table align=center border=4 cellpadding = 3 cellspacing=2><tr><td align=center> <b><a href="http://www.asi.org/index.html">ArtemisProject</a></b><td align=center> <b><a href="http://www.asi.org/asi_index.html">ArtemisSociety</a></b><td align=center> <b><a href="http://www.asi.org/adb/index.html">ArtemisData Book</a></b><td align=center> <b><a href="/adb/j/index.html">FAQ</a></b><td align=center> <b><a href="/adb/04/index.html">Reference Mission</a></b><td align=center> <b><a href="http://www.tlrc.com/catalog.html">Catalog</a></b></tr></table><hr size="5"><font size=1>Copyright &#169; 1996 Artemis Society International.Updated Fri, Apr 19, 1996<br>From <a href="mailto:LKlaes@aol.com">Larry Klaes</a>'s Planetary ProbeHistory section of the sci.space FAQ, with permission.<br>Content by Larry Klaes <ahref="mailto:LKlaes@aol.com">&lt;LKlaes@aol.com&gt;</a>, mainta