<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>M.8.5 Volatiles Present in the Lunar Regolith</TITLE></HEAD>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<!-- Artemis Data Book -->
<!-- ADB section M.8.5 Miscellaneous Minor Elements -->
<!-- file: /adb/m/08/05/volatile-table.html -->
<!-- Keywords: volatile regolith minor elements extraction gas heating
lunar industry -->
<!-- v 1.0 -->
<h2 align="center">Artemis Data Book</H2>
<h2 align="center">M.8.5 Miscellaneous Minor Elements</H2>
<h2 align="center">Volatiles Present in the Lunar Regolith</H2>
<P ALIGN=CENTER><I>Gregory R. Bennett</I></P>
<P><HR><P>

<P>Heating the lunar regolith has been shown to release these elements, as
well as others, in trace quantities.</P>

<BLOCKQUOTE><table>
<tr><td> <B>Element</B> </td><td> <B>Lowest</B> </td><td> <B>to</B>
</td><td> <B>Highest</B> </td></tr>
<tr><td> <a href="/adb/m/08/08/hydrogen.html">Hydrogen</a> </td><td> 0.001
</td><td> to </td><td> 0.20  %</td></tr>
<tr><td>   <a href="/adb/02/09/he3-intro.html">Helium</a> </td><td> 0.001
</td><td> to </td><td> 0.006 %</td></tr>
<tr><td>  <a href="/adb/m/08/08/carbon.html">Carbon</a> </td><td> 0.001
</td><td> to </td><td> 0.028 %</td></tr>
<tr><td>   Nitrogen  </td><td> 0.001</td><td> to </td><td> 0.016 %</td></tr>
<tr><td>  Zinc </td><td> 0.01 </td><td> to </td><td> 0.03  %</td></tr>
<tr><td> Sodium </td><td> 0.002 </td><td> to </td><td> 0.010 %</td></tr>
 <tr><td> Potassium  </td><td>0.002 </td><td> to </td><td> 0.010 %</td></tr>
<tr><td>  Chlorine </td><td> 0.002 </td><td> to </td><td> 0.010 %</td></tr>
<tr><td>  Flourine </td><td> 0 </td><td> to </td><td> 0.02  %</td></tr>
</table></BLOCKQUOTE>


