<H2>Mailbox</H2><P><HR WIDTH=80%></P>

<H3>Unmentioned advantage of shelter hangars</H3> <P align=center>10/2/95</P>

<P>&nbsp;&nbsp;One advantage of sheds or hangars as described in your recent
article, "Shelter on the Moon" [MMM #88, page 4] is that they would seem ideal
for inflatables. Think of it.</P>

<UL type=circle>
<LI>no thermal stress;
<LI>no exposure to UV or cosmic rays
<LI>no exposure to solar flares
<LI>no exposure to micrometeorites
<LI>no shielding emplacement pressure surges or trauma dangers 
<LI>lee environment for deployment
<LI>easy maintenance and access to exterior surfaces of inflatables 
</UL>

<P>&nbsp;&nbsp;The only problem I see for not-directly-shielded inflatables is a
slow buildup of corrosive atomic oxygen; but this seems unlikely in a "lee"
environment.</P>

<P> - Thomas Heidel, Milwaukee</P>

