<HTML><HEAD>
<TITLE>Moon Miners' Manifesto Issue #93</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<img src="/Gifs/artlogonb.gif" align=left alt="ASI Logo">
<!-- /093/osf.html -->
<h2 align=center>
This Month in the Artemis Society's Office of Space Flight
</h2><P><HR WIDTH=80%></P>

<P align=center><font size=+1 color="#FE2222">This file is <I>Not</I>
&nbsp;maintained. To see current information, please <br> refer to  the <a
href="/adb/06/07/osf-index.html" target="_top">Office of Space Flight
Organization Chart</a></font></P><br>


<P>&nbsp;&nbsp;We're finally getting the Technical Committees organized!
This month we collected all the information on who has volunteered for
which committee, and set up a structure for managing the work.</P>

<P>&nbsp;&nbsp;The Space Flight Technical Council is the core of this
organization, responsible for both the technical committees and the project
teams. NOTE: Where we haven't formally established agreements with the
supporting organizations, we're still listing Greg Bennett as acting in
those roles.[*]</P>

<H3>ASI Office of Space Flight - Technical Council</H3>

<B>Space Flight Development Members:</B>
<ul type=circle>
<li>Director, Office of Space Flight<br>
<a target="_top" href="bennett.gregory.html">Gregory Bennett</a> <a
href="mailto:grb@asi.org">&lt;grb@asi.org&gt;</a>
<li>Administrator, Technical Council<br>
<a target="_top" href="/bios/dicks.candace.html">Candace Dicks</a> <a
href="mailto:CDDicks@aol.com">&lt;CDDicks@aol.com&gt;</a>
<li>Administrator, Configuration Management<br>
Doug Cross <a href="mailto:DougCross@msn.com">
&lt;DougCross@msn.com&gt;</a>
<li>Director, Advanced Programs - (* Gregory Bennett, acting)
<li>Director, Mission Development
<br>Lou Ramon <a href="mailto:ramon#d#lou@ssdgwy.mdc.com">
&lt;ramon#d#lou@ssdgwy.mdc.com&gt;</a>
<li>Chairman, Mission Design Technical Committee
<br>Jim Sewell  <a href="mailto:sewell#d#james@ssdgwy.mdc.com">
&lt;sewell#d#james@ssdgwy.mdc.com&gt;</a>

